    "purpose": "Track quarter-over-quarter shifts in corridor-level yields, ADR, and occupancy. Use for trend analysis and underwrite-side seasonality calibration.",
    "scope": "Major Bali sub-zones only. Minor sub-zones tracked but not necessarily updated each quarter. Phuket retrospective TBD (insufficient direct data quarter-on-quarter at confidence level we maintain for Bali).",
    "delta_methodology": "Each `delta` field shows quarter-over-quarter change in PERCENTAGE POINTS for yield/occupancy fields, or in DOLLARS for ADR/price fields. Negative values are decreases.",
    "interpretation_guide": "Two consecutive quarters of yield decline at -0.5pp or more = structural softening, re-evaluate underwrite. ADR drift inside ±10% is seasonal noise. Occupancy drift inside ±3pp is seasonal noise."
